Question: https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-running-time-of-n-computers/

Solution:
class Solution {

    public boolean isFeasibleEnerygy(long total_energy_required,int n,int[] batteries) {
        long total = 0;

        for(int bat : batteries) {
            total+=Math.min(bat,total_energy_required);
        }

        return total>=total_energy_required*n;
    }

    public long maxRunTime(int n, int[] batteries) {
        if(n>batteries.length) return 0;

        long max_run_time=0;
        Arrays.sort(batteries);
        
        long sum_energy_given=0;
        for(int bat : batteries) sum_energy_given+=bat;

        long total_energy_required = sum_energy_given/n;
        
        long left=0,right=total_energy_required;

        while(left<=right) {
            long mid = left+ (right-left)/2;

            if(isFeasibleEnerygy(mid,n,batteries)) {
                max_run_time = mid;
                left = mid+1;
            }else {
                right = mid-1;
            }
        }

        return max_run_time;
    }
}

/*
   n = 2, batteries = [3,3,3] 
    computer : 1-> bat[0]
    computer : 2-> bat[1]
    // Note: we should not dry the battery in first cause that will give us the min_time so here the TLE is 3 so I can either stop it by time=1 or 2 wright ! ->max_runTime=2

    and now in this case I can't take 2 batteries at a same time because I just one battery left with me so I'll change any one battery lets say computer : 1->bat[2] {bat[0]:1} ->max_runTime=3

    and after this ! {bat[0]:1 , bat[1]:0, bat[2]:2}
    max_runtime can be of 1min so max_runTime=4 {Key: (min(1,2))}

    Technical workflow:

    initial_assignment : n-computers = n-batteries (here left out batteries-> 1) max_run_time=1
    // assign max batteries first to n computers 
    n=3, [10,10,5,3]
    assign n computers with ->[10,10,5] 
    max_run_time=4 {6,6,1} (switch 1 for 3, bat[2]=1)
    max_run_time=6 {4,4,2} 

    total_battery_flow = sum()
 */
